awards.title: Dean's List
awards.summary: The Dean’s List at Seattle University recognizes student academic achievement for undergraduates. To qualify for the Dean’s List, you must earn at least a 3.5 GPA for the quarter and have completed a minimum of 12 graded credits.

awards.title: Presidents's Scholar
awards.summary: Completion of 12 credits at the 100 level or higher during the quarter the award is given 3.9 to 4.0 college-level GPA

awards.title: Dean's List
awards.summary: Completion of 12 credits at the 100 level or higher during this quarter is given 3.5 to 3.89 college-level GPA
